public final class PolygonStyle
extends GenericJson

Represents a PolygonStyle within a StyleSetting

This is the Java data model class that specifies how to parse/serialize into the JSON that is transmitted over HTTP when working with the Fusion Tables API. For a detailed explanation see: http://code.google.com/p/google-api-java-client/wiki/Json

Author:
Google, Inc.

setResponseHeaders

public void setResponseHeaders(HttpHeaders responseHeaders)
Sets the HTTP headers returned with the server response, or null. This member should only be non-null if this object was the top level element of a response. For example, a request that returns a single PolygonStyle would include the response headers, while a request which returns an array of PolygonStyle, would have a non-null response header in the enclosing object only.
